    "body": "### Problem\n\nI want to disable fsync on a slow fuse-backed filesystem (it may hang for seconds on `:w`). I try to set it via `vim.bo.fsync`, but the option is not available: \"'buf' cannot be passed for global option 'fsync'\".\n\nIs it possible to make it per-buffer?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({'BufEnter', 'BufWinEnter'}, {  \n  callback = function(ev)   \n    local bufnr = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\n    vim.system(\n      {'arc', 'root'},\n      {cwd = dirname},\n      function(obj)\n        if obj.code == 0 then\n          vim.schedule(function()\n\t    vim.bo[bufnr].fsync = false\n\t  end)\n\tend\n      end\n    )\n  end\n})\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nper-buffer option is set\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ni don't know\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhttps://ppa.launchpadcontent.net/neovim-ppa: 0.11.0~ubuntu1+git202508130036-fece489794-545c88c787-b898809ed0~ubuntu22.04.1",
